{
  "body": "Because we are using \".allof\" to wait for Promises, we are losing the fact that some of the pod processing is erroring out. - allof just makes sure the promise ended, not that it worked.\r\n\r\nSo far I've found issues with files that have:\r\n\r\n```\r\n=head 3 C<thing>\r\n```\r\nand nested tags like:\r\n\r\n```\r\nX<C<a thing>>\r\n```\r\n\r\nBasically, there are several places in the code where we are assuming something is a Str, when in fact it's a Pod object.\r\n\r\n",
